1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson, we will explore WordPress block layouts.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,000
We will learn to nest and group blocks to create advanced layouts and block structures.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,000
As a reminder, we use container blocks such as the Group block, Columns block, Cover block, Media and Text block,

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,000
as well as Row, Stack and Grid blocks to nest blocks together.

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
A container block serves as a container or wrapper for other blocks,

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
allowing you to group related content and apply styles or settings to the entire group.

7
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,000
In the first example, let's recreate the following.

8
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
I have grouped a Header, a Separator and a Columns block together.

9
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
To start off, I will add a Group block and select a container.

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Then I will open up the sidebar settings and deselect 'Inner blocks use content width,'

11
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,000
as I want to change the width of the block.

12
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
And then I will use the block toolbar to change to wide width.

13
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
And then inside the Group block, I will add a heading and the relevant text.

14
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,000
And I will hold in shift and then enter to move to the next line.

15
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Below my heading, I will add a Separator block.

16
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
And in the block toolbar, I will change the style to wide line.

17
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,000
And below the Separator block, we can add a Columns block.

18
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
And select two equal columns.

19
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,000
And then add the text to the left and the right column.

20
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Now we can continue with styling.

21
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
Firstly, I will select the heading.

22
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:09,000
And then I'll open up my typography options.

23
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,000
And firstly select Appearance.

24
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
And change the appearance to thin.

25
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Then I will add a custom size.

26
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
In this case, five REM.

27
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
And finally, I will also change the lettercase to uppercase.

28
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Then I will keep the text in my left column the same.

29
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,000
But for contrast, I will change the size of the text in the right column to small.

30
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Then I will select the Group block or the container block.

31
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,000
And then add some padding or some space around the content of my Group block.

32
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
And then our first design is completed.

33
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
In the next example, we are going to recreate the following design based on one of the patterns available in the Pattern Directory.

34
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,000
The first step is to add a Cover block.

35
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:29,000
And then select a relevant overlay color.

36
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Then I will select the Cover block.

37
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Open up my sidebar settings.

38
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,000
And deselect 'Inner blocks use content width' as I want to change the width of the block.

39
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Then I will use my block toolbar and change the width of the block to full width.

40
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,000
The next step is to add a Row block.

41
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,000
And then to add a Group block.

42
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Then in the first Group block, I will add some text and below the text a call to action or Buttons block.

43
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
And I will type 'Explore.'

44
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Then I will style my Buttons block.

45
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,000
I will change the background color to black and the text to white.

46
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,000
I will also increase the size to medium and then change the letter case to uppercase.

47
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,000
Then I will select the Group block and then make my way to Styles.

48
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,000
I will change the block spacing between the two blocks in the Group block to 24 pixels.

49
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:20,000
And then I will change the width of the Group block to fixed.

50
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:27,000
And once we select Fixed we will see it says specify a fixed width.

51
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:32,000
And then we'll change the fixed width to 320 pixels.

52
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Next we'll select the Row block and then add another Group block for the text on the right.

53
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:51,000
And then add the name of the album I am highlighting in this section.

54
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,000
So I will type in 'on' and then hold in shift press enter, type 'in the', hold in shift press enter and then 'flame.'

55
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Next we will go ahead and select the text and then we can style it further.

56
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,000
So we'll make our way to Typography.

57
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,000
And in this case I am going to select Appearance, Line Height, Letter Spacing and Letter Case.

58
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
And then I will change the size of the text to 148 pixels.

59
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,000
And the appearance to bold, the line height to 0.8, the letter spacing to -4 pixels and the letter case to uppercase.

60
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:57,000
Then we can change the alignment of the text to right.

61
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
And to save time I am going to go ahead and duplicate the text and modify it accordingly.

62
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
Then we can select the Group block on the right, open up Styles and for this Group block below Width we will select 'Fill.'

63
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,000
And here we can read it says, 'Stretch to fill available space.'

64
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
And once we have done that we can make our way to settings and justify the items to the right.

65
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Then we can select the Row block again and in the block toolbar change the vertical alignment to align top.

66
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,000
Thereafter we can select the Cover block, open Styles and add some padding or space around the content of the Cover block.

67
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:03,000
And in this case I will change the padding to 5.

68
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,000
A final step to ensure that our design appears correctly on mobile is to select the Row block and then select 'Allow to wrap to multiple lines.'

69
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Now we can view our design on desktop and mobile.

70
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:30,000
In the last example we can recreate the following design using the Columns block.

71
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:36,000
So to start off let's add our Columns block and then choose 3 equal columns.

72
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:46,000
Then I will select the main Columns block or the container block and change the width to wide width.

73
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:54,000
Then I will select the first Column and add a Cover block.

74
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:03,000
And then select an image from my media library.

75
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Once inserted I will select the Cover block, open Styles, change the overlay color to black and the overlay opacity to 40.

76
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Then I will add a Stack block within my Cover block.

77
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,000
And within my Stack block I will add a Heading block, add the relevant text, select the text and then change the heading to uppercase.

78
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:55,000
Then I will change the size to 2 REM and also change the text to bold.

79
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Below my heading I will add a Separator block and below the separator a Buttons block.

80
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:17,000
And once I have added the Buttons block I will type in the text and then change the style to Outline.

81
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:25,000
And then I will also change the text to bold.

82
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,000
And don't forget to add the relevant URL.

83
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,000
Then I will select the Stack block and change the alignment to center.

84
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Then I will also open Styles and change the block spacing to 3 between the blocks in the Stack block.

85
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:46,000
Then we can select the Cover block and change the position of the content to top middle.

86
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,000
And finally we can add some padding around the content in our Cover block.

87
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:04,000
Then you also have the option to enlarge the size of your Cover block.

88
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:12,000
Now that the styling is completed we can select the left column and duplicate it twice.

89
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:26,000
And then we can delete the two empty columns.

90
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:36,000
Then we can merely update the content.

